body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

Run `synth_xilinx` for:

```
module top(...);

input [3:0] ra;
input [3:0] wa;
input [3:0] wd;
output [3:0] rd;
input we, clk;

reg [3:0] mem[3:17];

initial begin
        mem[3] = 3;
        mem[4] = 4;
end

always @(posedge clk)
        if (we)
                mem[wa] <= wd;

assign rd = mem[ra];

endmodule
```

## Expected behavior

`memory_bram` maps the memory to `RAM32X1D` with directly wired address and initializers going into `INIT` bits `3` and `4`

## Actual behavior

`memory_bram` maps the memory to `RAM32X1D` with directly wired address and initializers going into `INIT` bits `0` and `1`, resulting in missynthesis

